341
01:44:26,048 --> 01:44:30,409
So Model United Nations is an after-school club where students engage in discussions with other students.

342
01:44:30,829 --> 01:44:37,090
Students split up into several committee sessions to discuss different topics that could be real or fictional scenarios.

343
01:44:37,110 --> 01:44:43,331
They represent an entity that fits the topic, such as historical figures like George Washington, or a nation such as the United States.

344
01:44:44,091 --> 01:44:47,112
Students will collaborate towards a solution based on their beliefs.

345
01:44:47,512 --> 01:44:51,433
At Medford High, club members meet weekly on Mondays in our advisor, Mr. Brophy's room.

346
01:44:52,426 --> 01:44:57,595
to conduct committee simulation, reflect on conferences, and write position papers to prepare for future committees.

347
01:44:58,468 --> 01:45:04,051
In conferences, members address the problems presented to them and seek out a resolution to fix these issues.

348
01:45:04,391 --> 01:45:16,738
Throughout the 2025-2026 school year, Medford's Model United Nations Club has attended seven conferences, two of which being multi-day conferences where students spent three days fully immersed in the experience of a United Nations delegate away from home.

349
01:45:17,359 --> 01:45:24,603
At these conferences, Medford High School has won numerous awards, including Verbal Commendations, Best Position Paper, Outstanding Delegate, and Best Delegate.

350
