717
02:22:40,666 --> 02:22:52,735
This first slide that displays what was discussed just are the highlights in the last presentation around some of the challenges for school year 26-27 calendar as Labor Day is very late this year.

718
02:22:56,357 --> 02:23:10,984
It is September 7th, so that means that teachers report on Monday, August 31st for two days of professional development and students grades 1 through 12 plus do not start until Wednesday, September 2nd.

719
02:23:13,205 --> 02:23:24,088
And then Friday is a no school day, an observance of Labor Day per the collective bargaining agreement with teachers, making the last day of school set for June 23rd.

720
02:23:24,488 --> 02:23:31,290
That is without the five snow days that the Department of Education has us factor in, in case we need them.

721
02:23:31,810 --> 02:23:39,733
And as we reflect on this year, we needed four of those five days, thus moving the last day of school date up by four days.

722
02:23:41,506 --> 02:23:58,326
If we go to the next slide, part of the work that the district has done in partnership and collaboration with the Teachers Union was to talk about the challenges that arose around Good Friday and that it wasn't as simple as to say that

723
02:23:59,968 --> 02:24:12,312
We would recognize Good Friday as a school day off because per the five days that the Department of Education requires you to put in for snow days brings us exactly up to June 30th.

724
02:24:12,912 --> 02:24:14,333
So there was no wiggle room.

725
02:24:15,473 --> 02:24:26,697
I did present to this body and the community about the challenges and the data that the Good Friday Day provided to the district and the community.

726
02:24:28,173 --> 02:24:36,294
and reflected on our staff not being a true representation of the community population.

727
02:24:36,895 --> 02:24:42,236
And therefore, a lot of our staff members celebrate Good Friday.

728
02:24:43,036 --> 02:24:48,997
The work that we've done with the Teachers Union to get to an understanding is as follows.

729
02:24:49,277 --> 02:24:55,118
So Good Friday, which is March 26th, will now be a district-wide day off.

730
02:24:56,139 --> 02:24:56,960
School will be closed.

731
02:24:57,000 --> 02:24:58,924
It'll be a day off for students and staff.

732
02:24:59,686 --> 02:25:07,440
And then the previously planned March 2nd professional development day will now become a full school day.

733
02:25:08,697 --> 02:25:12,221
for students, teachers, and staff.

734
02:25:12,241 --> 02:25:25,154
And what we are doing with the time that was allotted on that professional development day is it is being divided up amongst the four remaining professional development days.

735
02:25:25,794 --> 02:25:30,639
And so that each of those four days, there are two before students start in August.

736
02:25:31,560 --> 02:25:37,688
one on the election day in November and then one on the Tuesday following Martin Luther King weekend.

737
02:25:38,169 --> 02:25:42,114
Those four professional development days will now go until four p.m.

738
02:25:42,575 --> 02:25:43,236
for staff.

739
02:25:44,632 --> 02:25:57,943
This was the recommendation and proposal of the teachers union and in collaboration with our district team felt that it was a wonderful solution to the challenge that we have for next school year.

740
02:25:58,604 --> 02:26:09,493
We love additional professional development time and adding that to an existing professional development day really allows a lot of breath and opportunity for the

741
02:26:11,554 --> 02:26:18,320
what we are going to have the teachers engage in, especially the two days in August as we're getting ready to kick off the year.

742
02:26:19,160 --> 02:26:25,285
That is the agreement that both sides came to in a memorandum of understanding.

743
02:26:26,066 --> 02:26:38,235
