And then we left in some of the list of expectations and then just put in here the email address to transportation just to make sure it was all aligned with the email address and the phone number so caregivers knew exactly

1072
03:00:30,955 --> 03:00:34,758
how to contact Ina Williams, our transportation supervisor.

1073
03:00:38,402 --> 03:00:41,364
I'm not sure if you want me to go to middle school.

1074
03:00:41,384 --> 03:00:49,532
I could just really briefly say, middle school, the language really remained the same except adding in the extension of the day

1075
03:00:50,489 --> 03:01:03,614
expectations from school to transport to and from as well as the surveillance language so that it's very clear for our middle school families that Eastern buses are equipped with surveillance.

1076
03:01:05,215 --> 03:01:07,756
And those are the updates to transportation.

1077
03:01:17,225 --> 03:01:28,104
So with the extension of the school day connotation in the student handbook, does that mean students can't use their phones on the bus?

1078
03:01:28,805 --> 03:01:29,106
Correct.

1079
03:01:30,382 --> 03:01:38,649
I find that to be a little unfair because if you're walking home or driving home, I feel like you get to use your phone.

1080
03:01:38,749 --> 03:01:52,962
So if you're walking, so that means I feel like if we put that into the buses, we would also have to kind of allow it to walking home and driving.

1081
03:01:52,982 --> 03:01:55,684
And I feel like that's kind of,

1082
03:01:57,065 --> 03:02:03,651
makes an unequal opportunity for the use of technology.

1083
03:02:04,171 --> 03:02:05,292
Do you understand what I mean?

1084
03:02:05,312 --> 03:02:06,993
I do.

1085
03:02:07,013 --> 03:02:08,695
I 100% know what you mean.

1086
03:02:08,715 --> 03:02:17,122
I think the difficulty is, and remember, Ryan, right now I'm talking about elementary and middle school, so I'm not talking about high school.

1087
03:02:20,064 --> 03:02:23,427
The difficulty is for in school,

1088
03:02:25,782 --> 03:02:27,484
Cell phones are often away.

1089
03:02:28,145 --> 03:02:31,828
They're not used while you're in school on the school bus.

1090
03:02:32,028 --> 03:02:44,601
I understand where you're coming from but unfortunately what happens sometimes is inappropriate use of the cell phone which could be that we have found that sometimes there's inappropriate use of what people are viewing.

1091
03:02:45,553 --> 03:02:51,921
inappropriate use of taking pictures or taking videos of other students without their permission.

1092
03:02:52,642 --> 03:03:02,014
And so I understand that this might be really upsetting for some students to hear, but it provides a layer of safety for everybody.

1093
03:03:03,095 --> 03:03:04,396
on that short ride home.

1094
03:03:04,936 --> 03:03:09,819
And then once they're home, the caregivers can decide how the phones are being used.

1095
03:03:10,180 --> 03:03:19,806
But it really provides just a clear expectation for all students about what their experience on the bus is going to be.

1096
03:03:22,808 --> 03:03:23,848
I have a suggestion.

1097
03:03:23,928 --> 03:03:36,355
How about discipline the certain student that is using the technology inappropriately and let all the other well-behaved students get that kind of reward.

1098
03:03:37,016 --> 03:03:44,000
And how about disciplining the certain student and maybe banning the student

1099
03:03:44,680 --> 03:03:52,562
from the bus or having them sit next to the driver and the driver monitors the situation.

1100
03:03:55,163 --> 03:03:57,464
Yeah, just an idea.

1101
03:03:57,484 --> 03:04:01,365
I understand that, and that's a great idea.

1102
03:04:02,205 --> 03:04:09,027
Unfortunately, it's not necessarily attainable on every single bus.

1103
03:04:10,286 --> 03:04:11,647
for elementary and middle school.

1104
03:04:12,607 --> 03:04:22,073
We're trying really hard to put monitors on buses that would be helpful to have an additional adult on the bus.

1105
03:04:22,133 --> 03:04:24,054
But some buses, it's just the bus driver.

1106
03:04:24,755 --> 03:04:31,099
And so it's really hard to know where that consequence would need to lay.

1107
03:04:32,019 --> 03:04:37,363
And sometimes what we also want to do is lessen any sort of like,

1108
03:04:38,243 --> 03:04:41,625
group mentality that could be targeted.

1109
03:04:41,645 --> 03:04:45,567
I have another question.

1110
03:04:45,647 --> 03:04:50,769
Why is this for the elementary and middle schools and not for the high school?

1111
03:04:50,789 --> 03:04:52,170
I'm just wondering.

1112
03:04:52,815 --> 03:04:54,156
That's a great question, Ryan.

1113
03:04:54,777 --> 03:04:59,480
So the majority of the high school busing is the MBTA.

1114
03:05:00,361 --> 03:05:05,986
And so that is not necessarily part of the extension here of Medford Public Schools.

1115
03:05:06,086 --> 03:05:08,668
So that is difficult for us.

1116
03:05:08,748 --> 03:05:14,953
We have expectations, but it's difficult for us to, it's even more difficult for us to monitor that.

1117
03:05:16,058 --> 03:05:25,084
Why is it difficult if it's running, if, so the bus makes a trip only for the high school students.

1118
03:05:25,265 --> 03:05:27,886
So I'm wondering why is that difficult?

1119
03:05:28,767 --> 03:05:33,490
Well, maybe I should know this, but sitting here right now, I'm not quite sure if MBTA has surveillance.

1120
03:05:34,951 --> 03:05:38,914
Like, I'm not quite sure if there's video or audio recording on an MBTA bus.

1121
03:05:41,296 --> 03:05:44,218
Or, yes, or if they would give us access to that recording.

1122
03:05:44,732 --> 03:05:47,074
And we have that with Eastern Bus.

1123
03:05:49,496 --> 03:05:50,137
All right.

