1236
03:15:24,098 --> 03:15:28,960
2026-13, resolution to establish a special education reserve fund for Medford.

1237
03:15:31,501 --> 03:15:33,322
Whereas the Medford Public School District

1238
03:15:34,828 --> 03:15:35,248
Thank you.

1239
03:15:35,308 --> 03:15:39,790
Motion to waive the reading by Member Graham, seconded by Member Reinfeld.

1240
03:15:39,850 --> 03:15:40,710
All those in favor?

1241
03:15:40,730 --> 03:15:40,790
Aye.

1242
03:15:41,451 --> 03:15:43,851
All those opposed?

1243
03:15:43,972 --> 03:15:45,472
The reading is waived.

1244
03:15:45,852 --> 03:15:47,453
If somebody could give an explanation.

1245
03:15:47,573 --> 03:15:51,815
I'll turn it over to you, Member Parks, as it's your resolution, if you don't mind.

1246
03:15:51,835 --> 03:15:53,275
Okay.

1247
03:15:53,875 --> 03:16:00,778
So this resolution is to establish a special ed reserve fund for Medford, which I learned about

1248
03:16:02,329 --> 03:16:15,916
when I was attending the charting the course training when I first started this role and basically it allows us to

1249
03:16:19,051 --> 03:16:41,408
put aside up to 2% of our total annual expenditures into a reserve fund, an interest bearing fund that can be used for unanticipated or unbudgeted costs of special ed services and programming out of district tuition for students.

1250
03:16:42,848 --> 03:16:50,392
special education transportation services and recovery high school program tuition.

1251
03:16:50,952 --> 03:17:08,480
And given that we have consistently seen fluctuating costs year over year and students move in mid year requiring these services.

1252
03:17:09,794 --> 03:17:12,475
And that has not been budgeted for at the beginning of the year.

1253
03:17:13,196 --> 03:17:19,198
This fund would be able to help offset those costs as it grows.

1254
03:17:20,159 --> 03:17:22,239
And so this resolution is to help with that.

1255
03:17:27,161 --> 03:17:29,903
Motion to approve by Member Reinfeldt, seconded by Member Graham.

1256
03:17:29,983 --> 03:17:30,703
All those in favor?

1257
03:17:30,723 --> 03:17:30,783
Aye.

1258
03:17:31,823 --> 03:17:35,685
Oh, wait, there is one correction, though, actually, in it.

1259
03:17:38,918 --> 03:17:40,679
Before the roll is called, Member Rousseau.

1260
03:17:40,699 --> 03:17:42,181
Thank you.

1261
03:17:42,301 --> 03:17:44,603
I'd like to amend 3E.

1262
03:17:46,105 --> 03:18:01,660
The current language is, current language is, any other permissible revenue, I'm sorry, 3E, other extraordinary expenses related to special education staffing, evaluation and assessment services.

1263
03:18:02,532 --> 03:18:25,599
What I would like to say is extraordinary expenses related to special education staffing, evaluation and assessment services that were not anticipated in the current fiscal year's operating budget provided that any such expense funded through the reserve shall be incorporated into the district's annual operating budget in the subsequent fiscal year and may not be funded through the reserve in consecutive fiscal years.

1264
03:18:26,139 --> 03:18:27,440
My concern is that we will

1265
03:18:27,840 --> 03:18:42,392
treat this like we do with other slush funds if you will revolving accounts and I don't if this year we need a new teacher because we have some new needs we absolutely that's the purpose of this next year.

1266
03:18:43,196 --> 03:18:47,377
Because we don't have enough money in the budget, that is not a use for this fund.

1267
03:18:47,777 --> 03:18:54,539
So looking at the law, the law doesn't say anything about this.

1268
03:18:54,619 --> 03:18:58,721
We literally could just fund our special ed department through this fund, which would be crazy.

1269
03:18:59,361 --> 03:19:04,522
And I want to make sure that whatever we do, we're making it clear that this is for this year only.

1270
03:19:05,183 --> 03:19:06,443
So that's my amendment.

1271
03:19:13,173 --> 03:19:15,895
The expenditure is just for that certain year?

1272
03:19:17,356 --> 03:19:19,979
So it's not for year over year cost is what you're saying.

1273
03:19:20,319 --> 03:19:33,330
I'm saying if you, you know, we have a student moves in and has a very specific special need and requires a certain kind of staff member and we hire them and the student is here next year too, that fund is not paying for next year.

1274
03:19:33,630 --> 03:19:34,991
That is an operating budget.

1275
03:19:35,011 --> 03:19:38,073
Yes, it's not an ongoing operating cost that we continue to take from.

1276
03:19:38,374 --> 03:19:38,514
Yes.

1277
03:19:40,319 --> 03:19:43,480
has to get into the budget no matter what on earth that means.

1278
03:19:45,701 --> 03:19:51,824
Which is my understanding of the intent of this, but it does feel like a little bit of an open door for maybe around 10 years.

1279
03:19:51,844 --> 03:19:53,544
No, that is the intent of it.

1280
03:19:53,664 --> 03:20:09,971
And that was also sort of the intent of putting in, maintaining a minimum balance in this fund so that A, there would be something that continuously collects interest in the account, but also to prevent it from drawing it down completely.

1281
03:20:13,542 --> 03:20:16,165
once we get it to that minimum place.

1282
03:20:18,227 --> 03:20:21,690
And if you accept it as a friendly amendment, then we don't have to... Yes.

1283
03:20:21,710 --> 03:20:21,891
Okay.

